channel.title: No-IP Help! My server won't go online!
channel.description:
Ok, so this usually works, but for whatever reason its not working this time... I have No-IP running, with several IP addresses as hosts, and I also have my server running. All of the people on my No-IP are smiling and blushing, which is what they are suppose to be doing, right? :confused: Well, nobody can log into my server, and its defiantly not online and I'm not sure why...
Can you help me? It would be greatly appreciated. ;D

item.title: No-IP Help! My server won't go online!
item.dc:creator: @life-scape life-scape
item.description:
@life-scape wrote:

[quote=“undertaxxx, post:6, topic:285580”]you can always check if the no-ip works by either pinging the no-ip host or do a tracert command in command.exe

Anyway, your problem seems to be the port. Check your firewalls/router etc. Also, let somebody try to connect to your server instead of just trying it from the computer/ip you’re serving with (some kind of TCP/UDP conflict idk.)

You can check if your port is open to others here:

http://www.canyouseeme.org/

=> Type in 43594 and check.

If you need any further help, let me know.

grtz~[/quote]

Ok i did that and when i check it on that website it says “Connection Timed Out”, so obviously it isn’t working, I did port forward it on my routers firewall, and on the router itself, what else is there to do? Please help!

Read full topic
